result.formatted_address: 226 Hollywood Rd, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Corner Kitchen Cafe

reviews.text:
Heard that Corner Kitchen Cafe serves one of the best grilled cheese in town. I have always wanted to try it out as I am a cheese lover. However, its location isn’t exactly convenient. I finally got a chance to try it out this week when I had some time (2 hours) for a meal before heading to gym in Central.

The cafe was quite full on a Tuesday late afternoon. Only one table was unoccupied. Not sure about second floor, but the staff said it would only be opened till 6pm, so I took the last table on the ground floor.

Cakes in the fridge looked so good. I made a mental note to visit again to try out these lovely cakes.

I came for the grilled cheese, and here it is! I paid HKD$18 for the fries and realized that there was actually too much carbs…Anyway, the spicy mayo was amazing!

The grilled cheese definitely lives up to its fame. Made with three kinds of cheese, the toast was absolutely fantastic! Bread was thick, fluffy and toasted with a crunchy top. Cheese was melted to the right point so that it wouldn’t be too solid/chewy to eat nor liquid to make a mess. Portion was quite huge indeed and left me really full even without the fries.

Nice little place in the heart of Sheung Wan. Super environment when it’s daytime, lots of lights everywhere in the restaurant so it feels always warm inside. The food is overall okay, not exceptional but it does the job. I especially like their chicken pesto sandwich and the bagels. They do offer as well vegetarian options to please all crowds.

I do recommend going there if you live close by, especially for your morning or weekend brunch routine. It is also a nice place to sit down, read a book or work on your personal projects on a computer
Food is nice enough if you want to pop by for a casual meal, but (unless it was just an off day) don't expect helpful service or engaging staff. I'd rather get barked at in a local HK style cafe.
Great atmosphere and food. Their cakes are amazing!
Clothes have strong oily smell after each visit, zero service as they don't charge for it. I would better off go somewhere else.
